4 HR____ COMMENDING HONORABLE JUDGE JODY BISHOP ON THE
5 OCCASION OF HIS RETIREMENT.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with highest commendation that Jody W.
8 Bishop is recognized for outstanding professional
9 achievement on the occasion of his retirement as Judge of
10 Alabama's 28th Judicial Circuit; and
11 WHEREAS, the Honorable Judge Jody Bishop has served
12 the people of Baldwin County and the State of Alabama with
13 exceptional dedication, integrity, and judicial prudence
14 throughout a distinguished career spanning multiple decades;
15 and
16 WHEREAS, Judge Bishop is concluding his second term
17 as Circuit Court Judge for the 28th Judicial Circuit, a role
18 to which he was re-elected in November 2018; his
19 distinguished judicial tenure also includes 12 years as
20 Presiding District Judge and three years as Municipal Judge
21 for the City of Fairhope; and
22 WHEREAS, prior to his judicial service, Judge Bishop
23 served the Baldwin County legal community as an Assistant
24 District Attorney and subsequently as the owner and operator
25 of a respected private law practice; and
26 WHEREAS, he has earned broad respect for his
27 unwavering commitment to professional excellence, as
28 demonstrated by his leadership as President of the Alabama
Page 1

demonstrated by his leadership as President of the Alabama
HR161 INTRODUCED
29 District Judges Association and his sustained engagement in
30 civic and community service; and
31 WHEREAS, Judge Bishop has demonstrated a steadfast
32 commitment to serving others through leadership roles with
33 the Kiwanis Club of Fairhope and the Eastern Shore, the
34 Board of Directors of the Boys and Girls Clubs of South
35 Alabama, the Fairhope Educational Enrichment Foundation, and
36 his current service on the Executive Board of Scouting
37 America, Mobile Area Council; and
38 WHEREAS, Judge Bishop is a graduate of Fairhope High
39 School, Berry College, and The University of Alabama School
40 of Law, and remains deeply rooted in the Baldwin County
41 community where he and his family reside; and
42 WHEREAS, Judge Bishop and his wife, Laura, are the
43 devoted parents of two children and are faithful members of
44 3Circle Church of Fairhope, where he serves as a greeter and
45 is active in his small group ministry, reflecting his
46 unwavering commitment to faith, family, and service; and
47 WHEREAS, Judge Bishop has earned immense respect for
48 his tireless dedication and exceptional abilities, and he is
49 truly deserving of special recognition; now therefore,
50 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
51 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That Judge Jody W. Bishop is highly
52 honored and commended, and this resolution is offered with
53 deepest admiration and appreciation for his immeasurable
54 service to the State of Alabama, as well as with sincere
55 best wishes for continued success in all future endeavors.
